subSubSection.paragraph:
Description. Character states of
Diamphidaxona (s. s.)
. Dorsal edge of camerostome rounded anteriorly and not projecting to anterior end of idiosoma (
Figs. 18, 21
). Pedipalps with tibia bearing one ventral seta and tarsus with ventral spine­like seta smooth (
Fig. 20
). Dorsal shield with anterior plate of same width as posterior plate and slightly pointed anteriorly (
Fig. 16
). Ventral shield with suture lines between third and fourth coxal plates with medial loops deeply arched and lateral loops U­shaped and open anteriorly (
Figs. 18, 21
). Projections covering insertions of fourth pair of legs with anterior extensions short and directed laterally to edges of ventral shield (
Figs. 18, 21
). Genital field of males separated from ventral shield by distinct band of membranous integument (
Fig. 18
).
